            "creation_date": 1414200937,
            "body": "<p>In general you can capture stack variables in Anonymous classes. Here's an example. I assume what you are trying to do will work.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class AnonymousTest {\n\n\n    public static void main(String[] args){\n\n        Object obj = someObject(\"Hey world!\");\n        System.out.println(obj);\n    }\n\n    public static Object someObject(String str){\n        return new Object(){\n            public String toString(){\n                return super.toString()+str;\n            }\n        };\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Output: stackoverflow.AnonymousTest$1@7f31245aHey world!<\/p>\n",
